{
  "texts": [
    "Each layer is followed by a nonlinear function called the activation function like sigmoid, relu, and tanh [48].",
    "• Convolutional neural network (CNN, or ConvNet): CNN, also known as ConvNet, is a type of deep neural network that is often used to analyze visual data.",
    "Video comprehension, audio recognition, and natural language processing (NLP) are among their numerous applications.",
    "In addition, combining LSTM with convolutional neural networks (CNNs) enhanced automatic image captioning, as demonstrated on Facebook.",
    "As can be seen, RNN aids us in data processing by predicting our next step, whereas CNN aids us in the visual analysis and automatic feature extraction [143]."
  ]
}